# E2E Verification (Mandatory)

**No task is complete until verified end-to-end.** "Should work" or "looks correct" is not done.

## Step 1 ‚Äî Automated gate (required)

Run **both** before marking complete. Fix failures before finishing ‚Äî do not hand off broken builds.

```bash
bun run lint
bun run build
```

Fallback order if `bun` missing: `npm run lint` ‚Üí `npm run build`.

If **all** runners fail in the environment: state exactly what was tried. Task is **blocked**, not done ‚Äî list what the user must run locally.

`build` includes TypeScript strict check ‚Äî type errors = build failure.

## Step 2 ‚Äî App smoke (every implementation)

After any non-trivial change, mentally or manually verify this path loads without console errors:

1. `/` ‚Äî login page renders
2. Login as **Rina** ‚Üí `/dashboard` ‚Üí `/chat` ‚Üí `/customers` ‚Üí `/settings`
3. Logout ‚Üí login as **Admin** ‚Üí same routes (supervisor view)
4. Logout ‚Üí login as **Pak Hartono** ‚Üí same routes (owner view)

Skip only if change is isolated to one route **and** you explicitly confirm others unaffected via grep.

## Step 3 ‚Äî Feature E2E (touching specific flows)

Execute the **full user journey** for what you changed ‚Äî not just the happy path click.

| Feature area | Minimum E2E flow |
|--------------|------------------|
| Login / roles | Select each agent ‚Üí Masuk ‚Üí correct dashboard scope |
| Dashboard | KPIs render, charts no crash, follow-up actions navigate to chat |
| Chat | Filter tabs ‚Üí select conv ‚Üí send message ‚Üí snooze/transfer/status if touched |
| Customers | Search ‚Üí filter segment ‚Üí open detail ‚Üí share modal if touched ‚Üí add customer submit |
| Settings | Open each section user role can access ‚Üí save/edit ‚Üí locked sections show empty state for CS |
| Store/types | All 4 main routes + login after data mutation |
| Permissions | Same action as CS (denied/masked) vs supervisor vs owner |

## Step 4 ‚Äî Regression checks

- No new `any` introduced (`type-strictness.mdc`)
- Forms show inline errors on invalid input (`validation-schema.mdc`)
- CS phone still masked where applicable
- Toasts in Indonesian, no console.error on happy path

## Definition of DONE (all required)

1. ‚úÖ `lint` passes
2. ‚úÖ `build` passes
3. ‚úÖ Smoke path (3 roles) for affected areas
4. ‚úÖ Feature-specific E2E flow documented in reply
5. ‚úÖ Known risks listed if something could not be run

## Do not

- Mark complete with only code review
- Skip build because "small change"
- Fix lint by disabling rules
- Leave `@ts-ignore` to make build pass

## Report template (include in every implementation reply)

